OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, John Lewis and the Co-op are both      
OL,6, raising minimum pay levels for workers 
OL,7, as retailers try to retain staff and   
OL,8, react to the rising living wage.       
OL,10,FJohn Lewis and Waitrose - both part of 
OL,11,Fthe same group - will lift pay for     
OL,12,Fstore workers to #11.55 an hour from   
OL,13,FApril, and to #12.89 in London.        
OL,15,FThis is above the compulsory National  
OL,16,FLiving Wage, which will increase to    
OL,17,F#11.44 per hour next month.            
OL,19,FThe Co-op will increase pay for 37,000 
OL,20,Fstore workers by 10.1% to #12 an hour. 
